title: Transactions Between Bernard Arnault and Russian Businessman Face Scrutiny
description: French prosecutors are looking at a 2018 real estate deal between the head of the LVMH luxury empire and Nikolai Sarkisov, a Russian insurance magnate.

title: What I’m Reading: Apples, Private Actors and Marina Abramovic
description: A retrospective of the performance artist’s work at the Royal Academy of Arts in London captures boundaries being violently tested and redrawn.

title: WSJ Reporter Evan Gershkovich’s Russian Detainment Reaches 6 Months
description: Evan Gershkovich’s father says “the feeling of helplessness is quite horrific,” but the family clings to hope.

title: Police Investigate About 100 Suicides Linked To Canadian Man
description: Canadian police charged Kenneth Law with aiding 14 suicides, including that of Ashtyn Prosser. Another 88 deaths are being reviewed by Britain’s National Crime Agency.

title: Ajax and the Fragile Business of Champions League Soccer
description: The stumbles of a famed Dutch club are a lesson in fallibility of even the best methods, and a reminder of how fast it can all go wrong at the top of the sport.

title: Putin Meets With Former Wagner Deputy
description: The Russian leader assigned Andrei N. Troshev, a veteran of wars in Afghanistan and Chechnya, with the task of forming volunteer units to perform combat missions for Russia’s war in Ukraine.

title: UEFA Opens a Door to Russia’s Return in Soccer, and Faces a Backlash
description: The angry reactions to a vote by European soccer’s governing body to partly lift its ban on Russian teams could be a preview of fights in other sports.

title: Bombing Kills at Least 52 at a Religious Gathering in Pakistan
description: The bombing, which officials believe was a suicide attack, was the latest sign of the country’s deteriorating security situation.

title: A Sri Lankan Baker’s Baguette Conquers France
description: After 17 years in France, Tharshan Selvarajah has yet to apply for citizenship. But he has made bread for President Emmanuel Macron.

title: How Palantir Became a Front-Runner for the UK’s Multimillion-Dollar NHS Contract
description: Palantir, the analytics company chaired by Peter Thiel, has courted N.H.S. England with pandemic help and assertive lobbying. Its big reward may be yet to come.

title: Armenia Finds Itself Cast Adrift in a Tough Neighborhood
description: While the Caucasus nation might want to reduce its reliance on Russia for a more reliable ally, Western nations have offered moral support but little else.

title: In Izium, Ukraine, Fear Remains a Year After Russian Retreat
description: In Izium, in eastern Ukraine, the buildings are in ruins and services are spotty. Barely recovered, its residents worry that more mayhem may lie ahead.

title: A Statue Draped With Snakes? In Italy, It Happens Every Year.
description: Held in a small, mountainous village, this festival has it all: snakes, charmers, religion, science. See for yourself — and try not to squirm.

title: Why Doesn’t Australia Have Better Trains?
description: And a glimmer of high-speed hope.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Forum in Kyiv Aims to Increase Weapons Production in Ukraine
description: Western officials and international arms manufacturers are set to meet as the country struggles to get its requests filled.

title: A U.S. Army hospital has quietly started admitting troops wounded in Ukraine.
description: The Army’s Landstuhl Regional Medical Center has quietly started admitting Ukrainian Army soldiers who were wounded in combat, most of them American volunteers.

title: U.A.E. Talks Peace in Sudan War, but Secretly Backs One Side
description: From a remote air base in Chad, the Emirates is giving arms and medical treatment to fighters on one side in Sudan’s spiraling war, officials say.

title: Friday Briefing
description: Sluggish progress in the war in Ukraine.

title: An Invasive Mosquito Threatens Catastrophe in Africa
description: A malaria-carrying species that thrives in urban areas and resists all insecticides is causing outbreaks in places that have rarely faced the disease.

title: Mosquitoes Are a Growing Public Health Threat, Reversing Years of Progress
description: Climate change and the rapid evolution of the insect have helped drive up malaria deaths and brought dengue and other mosquito-borne viruses to places that never had to worry about them.

title: The Gamble: Can Genetically Modified Mosquitoes End Disease?
description: Working on a remote island, scientists think they can use genetic engineering to block a malaria-carrying species of mosquito from spreading the disease — and do it in just a few months. But governments are wary.

title: One Village, Two Houses — and a New Tactic to Win the War on Mosquitoes
description: A different way of thinking about mosquito-borne diseases could save billions of dollars, and end them for good, some health experts believe.

title: Museum Worker Sold Paintings and Put Forgeries in Their Place
description: An in-house appraiser noticed something was awry when the canvas on his workbench did not match a catalog entry.
